OL,3,CReform promises tax cuts so big even
OL,4,CLiz Truss might think them gung-ho
OL,6,FThe problem is the Institute for
OL,7,FFiscal Studies (IFS) - which
OL,8,Fspecialises in UK taxation and public
OL,9,Fpolicy and is widely seen as both
OL,10,Fexpert and politically independent -
OL,11,Fsays Reform's plans "do not add up".
OL,13,FThe IFS says cutting #50 billion from
OL,14,Fgovernment departments would almost
OL,15,Fcertainly damage the quality and the
OL,16,Fquantity of public services.
OL,18,FAnd that blocking the Bank of England
OL,19,Ffrom paying interest to commercial
OL,20,Fbanks would raise less than half of
OL,21,Fthe #35 billion Reform is banking on.
